# Spec Skill: Structure

Generate a structure/anatomy spec frame directly in Figma for a given component node.

## When to use
User provides a Figma node URL (contains `node-id=`) and asks for:
- "structure spec", "anatomy spec", "spacing spec", "layout spec"
- "annotate this component", "spec this out"

## Steps

### 1. Read the component
Use `figma_get_component_details` with the node ID extracted from the URL.
If that fails, use `figma_get_file_data` to find the node.

Extract:
- Component name
- Layer hierarchy (children, their types and names)
- Width / height
- Padding values (paddingTop, paddingRight, paddingBottom, paddingLeft)
- Gap (itemSpacing)
- Layout mode (HORIZONTAL / VERTICAL / NONE)
- Fill/stroke colors (reference token names if available)

### 2. Take a before screenshot
Use `figma_take_screenshot` to capture the current state.

### 3. Build the spec frame via figma_execute

Run this pattern in `figma_execute`:

```js
// Find the target node
const target = figma.currentPage.findOne(n => n.id === 'NODE_ID_HERE');
if (!target) { figma.notify('Node not found'); return; }

// Create spec frame next to the component
const spec = figma.createFrame();
spec.name = `${target.name} — Structure Spec`;
spec.x = target.x + target.width + 80;
spec.y = target.y;
spec.resize(600, 800);
spec.fills = [{ type: 'SOLID', color: { r: 0.97, g: 0.97, b: 0.97 } }];
spec.layoutMode = 'VERTICAL';
spec.itemSpacing = 24;
spec.paddingTop = 32;
spec.paddingRight = 32;
spec.paddingBottom = 32;
spec.paddingLeft = 32;
spec.primaryAxisSizingMode = 'AUTO';
spec.counterAxisSizingMode = 'FIXED';

// Helper: add a label
function addLabel(parent, text, size = 12, bold = false, color = { r: 0.1, g: 0.1, b: 0.1 }) {
  const t = figma.createText();
  t.characters = text;
  t.fontSize = size;
  t.fontName = { family: 'Inter', style: bold ? 'Bold' : 'Regular' };
  t.fills = [{ type: 'SOLID', color }];
  parent.appendChild(t);
  return t;
}

// Helper: add a divider
function addDivider(parent) {
  const d = figma.createRectangle();
  d.resize(536, 1);
  d.fills = [{ type: 'SOLID', color: { r: 0.85, g: 0.85, b: 0.85 } }];
  parent.appendChild(d);
}

// Title
await figma.loadFontAsync({ family: 'Inter', style: 'Bold' });
await figma.loadFontAsync({ family: 'Inter', style: 'Regular' });

addLabel(spec, target.name, 20, true);
addLabel(spec, 'Structure Spec', 12, false, { r: 0.5, g: 0.5, b: 0.5 });
addDivider(spec);

// Dimensions
addLabel(spec, 'DIMENSIONS', 10, true, { r: 0.4, g: 0.4, b: 0.4 });
addLabel(spec, `Width: ${Math.round(target.width)}px  ·  Height: ${Math.round(target.height)}px`);

// Layout
if (target.layoutMode && target.layoutMode !== 'NONE') {
  addDivider(spec);
  addLabel(spec, 'LAYOUT', 10, true, { r: 0.4, g: 0.4, b: 0.4 });
  addLabel(spec, `Direction: ${target.layoutMode}`);
  addLabel(spec, `Gap: ${target.itemSpacing ?? 0}px`);
  addLabel(spec, `Padding: ${target.paddingTop ?? 0}px ${target.paddingRight ?? 0}px ${target.paddingBottom ?? 0}px ${target.paddingLeft ?? 0}px`);
}

// Layer anatomy
addDivider(spec);
addLabel(spec, 'ANATOMY', 10, true, { r: 0.4, g: 0.4, b: 0.4 });

function walkLayers(node, depth = 0) {
  const indent = '  '.repeat(depth);
  const typeTag = `[${node.type}]`;
  addLabel(spec, `${indent}${typeTag} ${node.name}`, 11);
  if ('children' in node && depth < 3) {
    for (const child of node.children) walkLayers(child, depth + 1);
  }
}
walkLayers(target);

figma.notify(`✅ Structure spec created for ${target.name}`);
figma.viewport.scrollAndZoomIntoView([spec]);
```

### 4. Take an after screenshot
Use `figma_take_screenshot` to capture the spec frame.

### 5. Validate
Check that:
- Spec frame appears next to the component
- Dimensions, layout, and anatomy sections are populated
- Text is readable

If anything looks wrong, use `figma_execute` to fix and re-screenshot (max 2 iterations).

### 6. Report back
Return:
- Before/after screenshots
- Summary of what was annotated (dimensions, layout values, layer count)
- Any missing data (e.g. node not using auto-layout)
